The most beautiful swimming pools in Europe
Jump in the water.
Julia Stanek
Children's swimming pools with universal fiber optics and stately pools in Budapest, where travelers can experience Europe's incredible water - and relax a tired body in a jacuzzi after a city tour or a walk.
One book can tell you where the best water is.
There's one thing Iris Meader couldn't do without during her exploratory trips the last year and a half: her swimsuit.
She lay on her back in the water, looking up at the tastefully decorated domes, swimming to the marble cherubs waiting for her at the edge of the pool and admiring the carefully restored ar-nuvo swimming pools.
She was quick to add every swimming pool she liked to her notebook - with important details about the building's construction and history.
Architectural historian Meder has explored more than 200 swimming pools - and now collects impressions in her recently published book Badefreuden (The Joy of Swimming), which includes everything from public swimming pools in Munich to historic swimming palaces in the Black Forest and "functional concrete buildings" in the Town.
