2011 - a year that will go down in Sinaloa's economic history as the first year of the government of Mario Lopez Valdés, also called the year of change, which generated great hopes for economic development, but given the unfavourable climate conditions of the beginning of the year, there was no growth, however, there was a decline in the main indicators of economic development.
