Park or mountain?
Architects agree with the competition after a dispute over the contributions
The municipal competition for 16 doors resumed debates on the role of Colserola in Barcelona
In the mid-1980s, at the height of the now-defunct Barcelona Capital Corporation (BCC), this administration printed promotional leaflets for the Colserola.
The booklet described the mountain as the great park of the capital Barcelona.
Moreover, it was accompanied by a picture comparison with Central Park in New York.
With the death of the SCB, in 1987 the park again took its place in the minds of many as the highest point of Barcelona as the capital of Catalonia, one of the few that is oriented not to the north-south, but up (mountain) -down (sea).
Positioning the Colserola as a nature park contradicts this idea.
The prototype wasn't Central Park, it was Yellowstone, with a wild boar as a Yogi bear.
That was until, in September, the council announced a huge competition consisting of 16 contests for many other gates in Colserolo.
The idea of a park is obviously a gate.
Either that or someone wants to put the gate on the field.
The question is, is it a roller coaster, a park or a mountain?
The competition, its organizational side and its impact on the city, is a topic for discussion among all Barcelona architects.
It's hardly the most frequent topic discussed when two members of this elite clan meet in an elevator.
And this fact leads to one of the few coincidences between what the three Barcelona architects and the scientists who were present said.
Miguel Roldan, Daniel Modolo and Mara Bayona: the competition is appropriate
For Roldán, after reaching the coastline, it becomes "necessary" to discuss the "front of the mountain", when the proposal of Ildefon Serda, the mountain with green apples, was not implemented.
"You have to admit that the biggest park in Barcelona is the beach.
And most of all, it's because of its excellent accessibility.
The Colserola is more complex", says the architect, for whom the title "Collserola Gate" contains a "word trap": we should not think of them "as a park entrance, but as a restriction of certain areas where we should act".
The model, like Roldán and Bayonne with experience in urban planning, called the proposal an "intellectual task" with "some dangers".
The risks arising from the "uncertainty of predicting public space" after the experience of the 80s, which ended on the Forum's platform with "its own swan song".
The first fear is actually limiting the boundaries that can be built.
"Limiting something is preparing for the next step", is the transition.
"We need to think about new urban planning tools because the current ones [as far as the General Capital Plan (GCP) is concerned] can lead to real trouble".
More specifically, Modolo believes that the simplification of the Val Colserola "can be understood as a park, not Barcelona" as a purely topographical matter.
Modolo recalls that there is already work being done outside of Calcerola, which "should not be missed", although he is grateful for the opportunity the municipality offers his professions to join this project "from the beginning".
Moreover, he understands that the proximity of the mountain to the city is a pass that allows architects to enter into the debate, but "he doubts" whether this technical profile is what should guide the interdisciplinary teams ("success", he claims) that were supposed to create: "Architects should only be a tool".
Byona suggests that the answer to the question that gives the title of this piece is complex, since the rules of the competition lack a common type of Colserola: "There have been 16 cross-contestations, he says, in the sense of a sea-mountain, but there is no long reading to see and understand the region as a whole".
That makes him decide to take part in at least 16 contests.
On the other hand, a project for one gate may intersect by program and definition with an architect's project for the neighboring gate.
In your view, the council is obliged to ensure that the strip directly above the Ronde de Dalt should provide a fully equipped area for a smooth transition between the city and the green.
